Explore the AWS Free Tier

 

Goal

:

In this section you will explore the different pricing tiers of the AWS product categories and perform a pricing estimate.

Outcome

:

At the completion of this section you will be able to estimate costs across the AWS products and services.

 

This lab is based on the online AWS getting started guide:

https://aws.amazon.com/getting-started/hands-on/control-your-costs-free-tier-budgets/

 

Access the Free Tier page

  1. Browse to the AWS Free tier Page 

Screenshot 1 – AWS Free Tier home page


Explore 12 month free offers

  1. Scroll down below to the “Free Tier Details.

 

  1. Under the “Tier Type” filter, tick the following checkboxes

Filter (check):

Tier Type

: 12 month free

Product Categories

: Compute

 

  1. You should see that you have 750 hours of free compute per month of Linux, RHEL, or SLES t2.micro or t3.micro instance dependent on region.

 

 

Screenshot 2 – AWS Free tier- EC2 and ELB

 

  1. Navigate to the Amazon Marketplace to look at a Free Tier application called “LAMP”.

 

Screenshot 3 – LAMP in Market Place is part of Free Tier

 

  1. Read the description in the Total Price window.

Many vendors offer products through Amazon market place that are part of the Free Tier. However the product will be based upon vendor recommended sizing of your virtual server (Instance type), in this case the instance type “t3a.small”.

 

These recommended sizing’s in general fall outside the free tier; you will have to explicitly select a t2.micro or t3.micro instance during the launch!


 

 

  1. Change your Free Tier Filter to:

 

Tier Type

: 12 month free

Product Categories

: Storage

 

  1. Read the Free Tier description for S3. You have 5 GB of Standard Storage with 20,000 Get Requests and 2,000 Put Requests

 

Screenshot 4 – AWS Free tier - Storage

Explore Always Free offers

 

  1. Change the Tier Type filter to explore the “Always Free” offerings with a popular product category:

Tier Type

: Always Free

Product categories

: Networking & Content Delivery

 

  1. Look at the search results once you have changed the filter.

There are no free “Networking & Content Delivery” products under “Always free”. However there are several AWS services part of “Networking & Content Delivery” that are always free. We will explore in the next step.

 

 

Screenshot 5 – AWS Free tier- Networking & Content Delivery

 

  1. Browse through the AWS Web page on Networking & Content Delivery and look at the services overview:

. Screenshot 6 – AWS Pricing Calculator

 

  1. Look at the Use case on “Build a cloud Network” the AWS Service “Amazon VPC”.

This service is required for ANY Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) deployment!

 

  1. Open the AWS calculator to estimate the costs for these services.


 

 

  1. Navigate in your browser to the AWS Calculator and click “Create Estimate”.

Screenshot 7 – AWS Pricing Calculator

 

  1. In the 2-step wizard, select the service and click “configure” in the VPC pane:

AWS Service

: VPC

Amazon VPC 

: Configure

 

Screenshot 8 – AWS Service costs: VPC

 


 


 

 

  1. In the 2-step wizard, configure your VPC as follows:

Region

: Your Region (in this example US East)

Connectivity

: Data Transfer

Inbound Data Transfer

: Internet

Inter-region Data Transfer

: 0

Outbound Data Transfer

: Internet

 

Screenshot 9 – AWS Service costs: Step 2 - Data Transfer Inbound

 

Screenshot 10 – AWS Service costs: Step 2 - Data Transfer Inter-Regional and outbound

 


 

 

  1. Look at the “total monthly costs”. The estimated costs should be “0”. 

From this calculator you can conclude that network services such as Internet Gateway, routing tables, security groups and other networking components not shown here are always free.

 

Screenshot 11 – AWS Service costs: Step 2 – Calculations
